Create <cok> package to **.packages**
This will create one package for the whole selected path including every assets and dependencies considered required for your assets by the game. No prefab processing will be done, but supports subfolders.
The packages will be available on the Editor on the Packages section in the Workspace. This is only an alternative to adding every assets one by one on the Editor Package Builder.

Rename prefabs safely by adding Obsolete Identifiers to the old name, so any assets placed with the older names works seamlessly as the renamed prefab.
A txt file is used to bulk rename prefabs. File location: **ModsData/StarQWorkflowKit_PrefabRenamer.txt**
The renamed prefabs won't be available in-game by default, since this will conflict with the original prefab files.

Options.OPTION[StarQWorkflowKit.StarQWor: Enable PrefabType based Category on startup
Options.OPTION_DESCRIPTION[StarQWorkflow:
Enabling this will add a new prefab category on the Editor/Dev Menu Add Objects panel, based on the prefab type. (Every game start as long as this is active)
{StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.EditorCatsWarning}
Options.OPTION[StarQWorkflowKit.StarQWor: Enable PrefabType based Category for this session only
Options.OPTION_DESCRIPTION[StarQWorkflow:
Enabling this will add a new prefab category on the Editor/Dev Menu Add Objects panel, based on the prefab type. (Only for this session)
{StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.EditorCatsWarning}
StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.PrefabMustBeActive:
Move all files you want to add to a separate folders in **ImportedData** and input that folder; which you can then take it to it's original folder.
** * **s are supported for paths like **\\A*\\B** or **\\A\\\\*\\B**.
Prefabs in this folder must be existing in the folder before the game is loaded. Will not work for disabled folders (with . or ~ in front). Will not work for folders outside the game's scope.
StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.ResaveReason: can be used in the event of changed prefab structure, resetting id/type after manually editing prefab, or to recreate CID if not found
StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.PrefabID: The PrefabID is the name of the prefab that is shown in the Editor's Edit Prefab list, not the localized name.
StarQWorkflowKit.Mod.EditorCatsWarning: IMPORTANT: Saving prefabs with this enable will have the category saved on the prefab file itself. Make sure to remove it manually before saving if you don't want it to be saved, or resave using the <Prefab Resave> buttons above.
